# Schema Documentation

z.email() is a validator that validates an email address, not z.string().email()
z.uuid() is a validator that validates a uuid, not z.string().uuid()

Reference: https://zod.dev/api

Example:

```typescript
const email = z.email();
const uuid = z.uuid();
```

If I teach you a new validator, please add it to memory. Stop using deprecated validators like z.string().email() and z.string().uuid().
